'''Niwica''' {{IPAr|pl|n|i|'|w|i|c|a}} is a [[village]] in the administrative district of [[Gmina Deszczno]], within [[Gorz<U+00F3>w County]], [[Lubusz Voivodeship]], in western Poland.<ref name="TERYT">{{cite web |url=http://www.stat.gov.pl/broker/access/prefile/listPreFiles.jspa |title=Central Statistical Office (GUS) - TERYT (National Register of Territorial Land Apportionment Journal) |date=2008-06-01 |language=Polish}}</ref> It lies approximately {{convert|10|km|mi|0}} west of [[Deszczno]] and {{convert|8|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-west of [[Gorz<U+00F3>w Wielkopolski]].

Before 1945 the area was part of Germany (see ''[[Territorial changes of Poland after World War II]]'').

